{
  "text": "We first recall the notion of K-step opacity [CITATION_1] ]. Definition 1. (K-Step Opacity). Given a (possibly nondeterministic) finite automaton G = (X, \u03a3, \u03b4, X 0 ), a projection map P with respect to the set of observable events \u03a3 obs (\u03a3 obs \u2286 \u03a3), and a set of secret states S \u2286 X, automaton G is K-step opaque (for some K \u2265 0) with respect to S and P (or (S, P, K)-opaque), if for all t \u2208 \u03a3 * , t \u2032 \u2208t, and i \u2208 X 0 ,",
